						<tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">1</div> <div class="vers-content">Hi sunt ergo principes familiarum, et genealogia eorum, qui ascenderunt mecum in regno Artaxerxis regis de Babylone.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">1</div> <div class="vers-content">Now  these are the chiefs of families, and the genealogy of them, who came up with me from Babylon in the reign of Artaxerxes the king.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">1</div> <div class="vers-content">The leaders, who took part with me in this migration under Artaxerxes, were descended as follows:</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">2</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Phinees, Gersom. De filiis Ithamar, Daniel. De filiis David, Hattus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">2</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Phinees, Gersom. Of the sons of Ithamar, Daniel. Of the sons of David, Hattus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">2</div> <div class="vers-content">Gersom was of the stock of Phinees, Daniel of Ithamar, Hattus of David.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">3</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Secheniæ, filiis Pharos, Zacharias: et cum eo numerati sunt viri centum quinquaginta.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">3</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Sechenias, the son of Pharos, Zacharias, and with him were numbered a hundred and fifty men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">3</div> <div class="vers-content">These were the numbers the various clans provided: Pharos (of the sons of Sechenias), a hundred and fifty under Zacharias;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">4</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Phahath Moab, Elioënai filius Zarehe, et cum eo ducenti viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">4</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Phahath Moab, Eleoenai the son of Zareha, and with him two hundred men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">4</div> <div class="vers-content">Phahath-Moab, two hundred under Elioenai, son of Zarehe;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">5</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Secheniæ, filius Ezechiel, et cum eo trecenti viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">5</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Sechenias, the son of Ezechiel, and with him three hundred men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">5</div> <div class="vers-content">Sechenias, three hundred under …, son of Ezechiel;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">6</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Adan, Abed filius Jonathan, et cum eo quinquaginta viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">6</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Adan, Abed the son of Jonathan, and with him fifty men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">6</div> <div class="vers-content">Adan, fifty under Abed son of Jonathan;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">7</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Alam, Isaias filius Athaliæ, et cum eo septuaginta viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">7</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Alam, Isaias the son of Athalias, and with him seventy men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">7</div> <div class="vers-content">Alam, seventy under Isaias son of Athalias;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">8</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Saphatiæ, Zebedia filius Michaël, et cum eo octoginta viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">8</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Saphatia: Zebodia the son of Michael, and with him eighty men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">8</div> <div class="vers-content">Saphatia, eighty under Zebedia son of Michael;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">9</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Joab, Obedia filius Jahiel, et cum eo ducenti decem et octo viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">9</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Joab, Obedia the son of Jahiel, and with him two hundred and eighteen men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">9</div> <div class="vers-content">Joab, two hundred and eighteen under Obedia son of Jahiel;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">10</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Selomith, filius Josphiæ, et cum eo centum sexaginta viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">10</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Selomith, the son of Josphia, and with him a hundred and sixty men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">10</div> <div class="vers-content">Selomith, a hundred and sixty under …, son of Josphia;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">11</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Bebai, Zacharias filius Bebai, et cum eo viginti octo viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">11</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Bebai, Zacharias the son of Bebai: and with him eight and twenty men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">11</div> <div class="vers-content">Bebai, twenty-eight under Bebai’s son Zacharias;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">12</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Azgad, Johanan filius Eccetan, et cum eo centum et decem viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">12</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Azgad, Joanan the son of Eccetan, and with him a hundred and ten men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">12</div> <div class="vers-content">Azgad, a hundred and ten under Johanan son of Eccetan;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">13</div> <div class="vers-content">De filiis Adonicam, qui erant novissimi: et hæc nomina eorum: Elipheleth, et Jehiel, et Samaias, et cum eis sexaginta viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">13</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Adonicam, who were the last: and these are their names: Eliphelet, and Jehiel, and Samaias, and with them sixty men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">13</div> <div class="vers-content">Adonicam, sixty, under his last remaining sons, Elipheleth, Jehiel and Samaias;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">14</div> <div class="vers-content">De filii Begui, Uthai et Zachur, et cum eis septuaginta viri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">14</div> <div class="vers-content">Of the sons of Begui, Uthai and Zachur, and with them seventy men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">14</div> <div class="vers-content">Begui, seventy under Uthai and Zachur.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">15</div> <div class="vers-content">Congregavi autem eos ad fluvium qui decurrit ad Ahava, et mansimus ibi tribus diebus: quæsivique in populo et in sacerdotibus de filiis Levi, et non inveni ibi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">15</div> <div class="vers-content">And I gathered them together to the river, which runneth down to Ahava, and we stayed there three days: and I sought among the people and among the priests for the sons of Levi, and found none there.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">15</div> <div class="vers-content">We made a halt of three days by the Ahava river; and there I found that I had common folk with me and priests, but no Levites.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">16</div> <div class="vers-content">Itaque misi Eliezer, et Ariel, et Semeiam, et Elnathan, et Jarib, et alterum Elnathan, et Nathan, et Zachariam, et Mosollam principes: et Jojarib, et Elnathan sapientes.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">16</div> <div class="vers-content">So I sent Eliezer, and Ariel, and Semeias, and Elnathan, and Jarib, and another Elnathan, and Nathan, and Zacharias, and Mosollam, chief men: and Joiarib, and Elnathan, wise men.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">16</div> <div class="vers-content">So I despatched some of the chiefs, Eliezer, Ariel, Semeias, Elnathan, Jarib, (a second Elnathan,) Nathan, Zacharias and Mosollam, with two prudent counsellors, Joiarib and Elnathan,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">17</div> <div class="vers-content">Et misi eos ad Eddo, qui est primus in Chasphiæ loco, et posui in ore eorum verba, quæ loquerentur ad Eddo, et fratres ejus Nathinæos in loco Chasphiæ, ut adducerent nobis ministros domus Dei nostri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">17</div> <div class="vers-content">And I sent them to Eddo, who is chief in the place of Chasphia, and I put in their mouth the words that they should speak to Eddo, and his brethren the Nathinites in the place of Chasphia, that they should bring us ministers of the house of our God.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">17</div> <div class="vers-content">to Eddo, who was in command at Casphia; I bade them ask Eddo and the Nathinaeans who were there with him to supply us with ministers for the house of our God.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">Et adduxerunt nobis per manum Dei nostri bonam super nos, virum doctissimum de filiis Moholi filii Levi, filii Israël, et Sarabiam et filios ejus et fratres ejus decem et octo,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">And by the good hand of our God upon us, they brought us a most learned man of the sons of Moholi the son of Levi the son of Israel, and Sarabias and his sons, and his brethren eighteen,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">And they, by God’s favour, sent us …, a Levite of Moholi’s clan, with Sarabias and eighteen more of his kinsmen;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">et Hasabiam, et cum eo Isaiam de filiis Merari, fratresque ejus, et filios ejus viginti:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">And Hasabias, and with him Isaias of the sons of Merari, and his brethren, and his sons twenty.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">19</div> <div class="vers-content">also a Merarite, Hasabias, with Isaias and twenty more of his.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">et de Nathinæis, quos dederat David et principes ad ministeria Levitarum, Nathinæos ducentos viginti: omnes hi suis nominibus vocabantur.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">And of the Nathinites, whom David, and the princes gave for the service of the Levites, Nathinites two hundred and twenty: all these were called by their names.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">There were also two hundred and twenty Nathinaeans; these Nathinaeans were men bound over by David and David’s councillors to the service of the Levites. A list of all their names was supplied to us.  </div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">Et prædicavi ibi jejunium juxta fluvium Ahava, ut affligeremur coram Domino Deo nostro, et peteremus ab eo viam rectam nobis et filiis nostris, universæque substantiæ nostræ.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">And I proclaimed there a fast by the river Ahava, that we might afflict ourselves before the Lord our God, and might ask of him a right way for us and for our children, and for all our substance.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">There, by the Ahava river, I proclaimed a fast; we would do penance, and ask of the Lord our God a safe journey for ourselves, for the children who went with us, and for all that was ours.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">Erubui enim petere a rege auxilium et equites, qui defenderent nos ab inimico in via: quia dixeramus regi: Manus Dei nostri est super omnes qui quærunt eum in bonitate: et imperium ejus, et fortitudo ejus, et furor, super omnes qui derelinquunt eum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">For I was ashamed to ask the king for aid and for horsemen, to defend us from the enemy in the way: because we had said to the king: The hand of our God is upon all them that seek him in goodness: and his power and strength, and wrath upon all them that forsake him.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">I would have asked the king for an escort of horsemen to defend us from attack, but shame withheld me; had we not boasted in the king’s presence that our God graciously protected all who had recourse to him, that only faithless servants of his brought down on themselves the constraining power of his vengeance?</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">Jejunavimus autem, et rogavimus Deum nostrum per hoc: et evenit nobis prospere.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">And we fasted, and besought our God for this: and it fell out prosperously unto us.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">So fast we did, to win the favour we asked of God, and all went well.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Et separavi de principibus sacerdotum duodecim, Sarabiam, et Hasabiam, et cum eis de fratribus eorum decem:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">And I separated twelve of the chief of the priests, Sarabias, and Hasabias, and with them ten of their brethren,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Then I chose twelve of the leading priests, Sarabias and Hasabias with ten others,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">appendique eis argentum et aurum, et vasa consecrata domus Dei nostri, quæ obtulerat rex et consiliatores ejus, et principes ejus, universusque Israël eorum qui inventi fuerant:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">And I weighed unto them the silver and gold, and the vessels consecrated for the house of our God, which the king and his counsellors, and his princes, and all Israel, that were found had offered.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">and handed over to them the offerings made by king, councillors, and nobles, and by such Israelites as came forward with gifts; the whole weight of silver and gold, and all the hallowed appurtenances of our God’s temple.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">et appendi in manibus eorum argenti talenta sexcenta quinquaginta, et vasa argentea centum, auri centum talenta:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">And I weighed to their hands six hundred and fifty talents of silver, and a hundred vessels of silver, and a hundred talents of gold,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">It was six hundred and fifty talents of silver I paid over to them, with a hundred pieces of silver ware; and a hundred talents of gold,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">et crateres aureos viginti, qui habebant solidos millenos, et vasa æris fulgentis optimi duo, pulchra ut aurum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">And twenty cups of gold, of a thousand solids, and two vessels of the best shining brass, beautiful as gold.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">with twelve bowls of the same metal, each of ten pounds’ weight, and two pieces of the finest bronze ware, like gold itself for beauty.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Et dixi eis: Vos sancti Domini, et vasa sancta, et argentum et aurum, quod sponte oblatum est Domino Deo patrum nostrorum:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">And I said to them: You are the holy ones of the Lord, and the vessels are holy, and the silver and gold, that is freely offered to the Lord the God of our fathers.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">You are consecrated to the Lord, I told them, and here are consecrated things; here are silver and gold offered as a free gift to the Lord God of our fathers.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">vigilate et custodite, donec appendatis coram principibus sacerdotum, et Levitarum, et ducibus familiarum Israël in Jerusalem, in thesaurum domus Domini.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Watch ye and keep them, till you deliver them by weight before the chief of the priests, and of the Levites, and the heads of the families of Israel in Jerusalem, into the treasure of the house of the Lord.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Keep watchful guard over them; you are answerable for delivering them safely, in the presence of priest and Levite and clan chief there in Jerusalem, into the treasury of our God.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">Susceperunt autem sacerdotes et Levitæ pondus argenti, et auri, et vasorum, ut deferrent Jerusalem in domum Dei nostri.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">And the priests and the Levites received the weight of the silver and gold, and the vessels, to carry them to Jerusalem to the house of our God.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">So these priests and Levites took all that weight of silver and gold into their keeping, and the ornaments besides, that must be brought safely to the house of our God at Jerusalem.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">Promovimus ergo a flumine Ahava duodecimo die mensis primi ut pergeremus Jerusalem: et manus Dei nostri fuit super nos, et liberavit nos de manu inimici et insidiatoris in via.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">Then we set forward from the river Ahava on the twelfth day of the first month to go to Jerusalem: and the hand of our God was upon us, and delivered us from the hand of the enemy, and of such as lay in wait by the way.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">We left the Ahava river on the twelfth day of the first month, bound for Jerusalem; and, with our God protecting us from all peril on the way, of open enemy or secret,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">Et venimus Jerusalem, et mansimus ibi tribus diebus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">And we came to Jerusalem, and we stayed there three days.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">to Jerusalem we came. We had been there but three days</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Die autem quarta appensum est argentum, et aurum, et vasa in domo Dei nostri per manum Meremoth filii Uriæ sacerdotis, et cum eo Eleazar filius Phinees, cumque eis Jozabed filius Josue, et Noadaia filius Bennoi Levitæ,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">And on the fourth day the silver and the gold, and the vessels were weighed in the house of our God by the hand of Meremoth the son of Urias the priest, and with him was Eleazar the son of Phinees, and with them Jozabad the son of Josue, and Noadaia the son of Benoi, Levites.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">before silver, gold and ornaments, were delivered safe in our God’s temple. Meremoth, son of the priest Urias, and Eleazar, son of Phinees, with two Levites, Jozabed son of Josue and Noadaia son of Bennoi,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">juxta numerum et pondus omnium: descriptumque est omne pondus in tempore illo.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">According to the number and weight of every thing: and all the weight was written at that time.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">handed it over, all counted and weighed, and its weight was duly entered.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">Sed et qui venerant de captivitate filii transmigrationis, obtulerunt holocautomata Deo Israël, vitulos duodecim pro omni populo Israël, arietes nonaginta sex, agnos septuaginta septem, hircos pro peccato duodecim: omnia in holocaustum Domino.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">Moreover the children of them that had been carried away that were come out of the captivity, offered holocausts to the God of Israel, twelve calves for all the people of Israel, ninety-six rams, seventy-seven lambs, and twelve he goats for sin: all for a holocaust to the Lord.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">35</div> <div class="vers-content">And these exiles, restored now from captivity, offered the God of Israel burnt-sacrifice; twelve calves for the twelve tribes of Israel, ninety rams and seventy-seven lambs, besides twelve goats as an offering for fault. Such was the burnt-sacrifice they made in the Lord’s honour;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">Dederunt autem edicta regis satrapis qui erant de conspectu regis, et ducibus trans flumen, et elevaverunt populum et domum Dei.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">And they gave the king’s edicts to the lords that were from the king’s court, and the governors beyond the river, and they furthered the people and the house of God.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">36</div> <div class="vers-content">then they delivered the royal edict to the governors, that were the king’s officers; and now God’s people and God’s house were held in honour by all that bore rule in the country west of Euphrates.</div></div></td>
								</tr>					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
